OUTTAKES: QUIBBLES &amp; BITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Last week, we referred to a CBS miniseries on the Walker spy ring as "Family of 
Five." It should have been "Family of Spies." Sorry! 
</P>
<P>
Julian Schlossberg, business rep for Elaine May stated that, contrary to a 
reference in Calendar, his client had "nothing to do with the 'Dick Tracy' 
script" currently being filmed by Warren Beatty. 
</P>
<P>
. . . KTTV News tried to pass off as news coverage a shameless hype job on the 
Fox syndicated show "Cops" -- which aired, of course, on KTTV. 
</P>
<P>
. . . KABC's garrulous Gary Franklin tells us about popping into a Cannon-owned 
porn theater in Glasgow while on vacation -- and finding that "all the 
(hard-core) sex scenes had been cut" from the film. Returning Stateside, he 
called Cannon to complain about not getting his money's worth. Postscript: 
Cannon sent him a 5 note! 
</P>
