<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE CIRCUS AS ART 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Regarding "The Circus as Serious Art" (Dec. 11): Just what qualifies a circus 
to be compared to ballet or opera as "art"? No singer or dancer is beaten or 
tormented to do totally unnatural acts; no one forces an artist to perform. 
</P>
<P>
The animals forced to do acts that violate nature and their dignity are not 
given a choice. I hate circuses because of the suffering, physical and 
emotional, the animals endure. 
</P>
<P>
BEATRICE J. SIMPSON 
</P>
<P>
South Pasadena 
</P>
</TEXT>
