</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
May I nit-pick a bit? Reference is made several times to a Marshall eagle. The 
eagle shown with Hubert Wells is a martial eagle. I have seen several of them 
in Africa, and I guess that martial in this sense means warlike, for they are 
highly effective killers of smaller birds. 
</P>
<P>
JOHN WELLS IREYS 
</P>
<P>
Beverly Hills 
</P>
