<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEW BOOKS: AROUND HOME; 
</P>
<P>
THE COMPLETE BOOK OF DECORATIVE PAINT TECHNIQUES BY ANNIE SLOAN AND KATE GWYNN 
(SALEM HOUSE; 1988) 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Virginia Gray 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PAINT, THE MOST versatile and affordable decorating tool, can be used in 
traditional, contemporary, artful, whimsical or zany applications. Here's a 
comprehensive guide for those who may attempt their own decorative painting on 
walls, ceilings, woodwork or furniture. Each technique is clearly illustrated 
step-by-step in color photographs. What the authors call basic finishes -- 
sponging, mutton clothing, ragging, color washing, combing, spattering -- are 
dealt with first. Then comes information on more advanced techniques -- gesso, 
marbling, porphyry, granite, moire, tortoise shell, wood finishes, wood 
graining, and gold leaf. A glossary further explains terms and techniques. 
($29.95) Virginia Gray 
</P>
