<P>
Photo, $500-Million City Within a City: Montage shows 6.3-acre Metropolis 
development proposed for site bounded by 8th, 9th and Francisco streets and 
Harbor Freeway, foreground. The 2.6-million-square-foot master plan, awaiting 
final CRA approval, includes three 30-story office towers, a 500-room hotel and 
retail center. Parkhill Partners would develop parcel for City Centre 
Development, property owner. First 635,000-square-foot office building 
(Metropolis Phase 1) is slated to begin construction this year, with occupancy 
in 1991. Michael Graves of Princeton, N.J., is architect. 
</P>
