<P>
Photo, Medical magnet -- Work has begun on the Los Angeles Unified School 
District's $25-million medical magnet high school at 1200 N. Cornwell St., 
Boyle Heights. The school, for students planning to enter the health 
profession, will open by fall, 1990. Architects of the facility are Flewelling 
&amp; Moody, Eagle Rock, and Miralles Associates, Altadena. Contractor of the 
district's first new high school in 17 years is Stolte Construction, Los 
Angeles. 
</P>
