<HEADLINE>
<P>
RENOVATION SET FOR INDIO MALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Construction will begin in March on a $30-million renovation and expansion of 
Indio Fashion Mall designed by McClellan Cruz Gaylord &amp; Associates and 
developed by William J. Stone &amp; Associates. 
</P>
<P>
Expansion will include 110,000 square feet of new shops and common areas, and 
an additional 113,000 square feet that will include a multiplex cinema, a 
50,000-square-foot J.C. Penney and 37,000 square feet of restaurant and retail 
space. Total square footage at completion is estimated at 600,000. 
</P>
<P>
A design focus is an existing barrel-vaulted ceiling at the main entrance and 
skylights throughout the mall. Leasing is being handled by the Riverside office 
of Coldwell Banker. 
</P>
</TEXT>
