ICE CREAM TO BE PRODUCED IN BIG SCOOPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Carnation Co. of Los Angeles has opened an $80-million, 225,000-square-foot ice 
cream plant at 3701 District Blvd., Bakersfield, that is as big as five 
football fields. 
</P>
<P>
Dick Curd, Carnation spokesman, described the plant as the "world's biggest." 
</P>
<P>
The plant was designed and built by A. Epstein &amp; Sons of Chicago. 
</P>
