KATELL ANNOUNCES NEW PHASES FOR TECHNOLOGY PARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Katell Properties/CalFed Enterprises partnership has announced new phases 
in the development of the 28-acre Valencia Technology Park, adjacent to 
Interstate 5 at the California 126 off-ramp and the largest mixed-use park in 
the Valencia Industrial Center. 
</P>
<P>
Katell/CalFed has completed construction of an $8.7-million 
manufacturing/distribution facility at the site and will break ground this 
month and next on two additional projects. 
</P>
<P>
Ground will be broken this month for a $4.5-million, one-story headquarters and 
manufacturing facility for Paragon Precision Products. A $1.6-million, 
23,500-square-foot facility for GG Industries will get under way in February. 
</P>
