PROJECT UNDER WAY IN SANTA MONICA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lincoln Place,, a $7.5-million office/retail building being developed by 
Lincoln Place Associates, is under construction on the northwest corner of 
Lincoln Boulevard and Arizona Avenue in Santa Monica. The 38,800-square-foot 
building will feature 8.500 square feet of retail space on the ground level, 
with the remaining three levels planned for offices. The architect is 
Matlin+Dvoretzky architects; the general contractor is Morley Construction Co. 
and financing is being provided by Santa Monica Bank. 
</P>
