<HEADLINE>
<P>
'LETTER' TO EX-PRESIDENT PRAISED FOR ITS HONESTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sam Hall Kaplan's column (Jan. 22) on ex-President Reagan was a breath of fresh 
air, truth, honesty, etc. after the stifling accolade given to this, our worst 
President in the history of our republic. 
</P>
<P>
Thank God that the infamous Ron and Nancy dog and pony show has closed its run. 
He can no longer veto sound legislation that fails to fit into his shallow, 
inhumane ideology. 
</P>
<P>
I hope that you will continue to write on the subject of Reagan's illusions. 
The American people are being cruelly deceived by this amiable dunce. 
</P>
<P>
JOHN UTVICH 
</P>
<P>
San Marino 
</P>
<P>
Letters to "Our Readers Write" must include the writer's name, address and 
daytime telephone number and should be sent to the Real Estate Editor, Los 
Angeles Times, Times Mirror Square, Los Angeles 90053. Letters may be edited 
for reasons of space and clarity. 
</P>
</TEXT>
