</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLDLY MIX 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Kathie Jenkins 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Feeling cosmopolitan? 
</P>
<P>
Austria: Barnabey's Restaurant, 3501 N. Sepulveda Blvd., Manhattan Beach, (213) 
545-8466. Style: Viennese neue Kuche in Gold Rush splendor. Setting: Heavy 
Victorian clutter, semi-private booths with phone jacks and heavy hitters. 
Recommended dishes: Venison steak; rabbitburger; Tyrolean mushrooms. Cost: 
$18-$40. 
</P>
<P>
Brazil: Cafe Connection, 9171 Wilshire Blvd., Beverly Hills, (213) 271-9545. 
Style: All-American cafe that cooks up "Brazil" on Thursday, Friday and 
Saturday nights. Setting: Plush coffee shop combo throbs sambas and lots of 
cosmopolitan kissy-kissy. Recommended dishes: Camarao Paulista (Brazilian 
scampi); feijoada (a hefty stew); bolinhos de bacalhau (codfish croquettes). 
Cost: $10-$20. 
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia: Red Sea Ethiopian Restaurant, 1551 Ocean Ave., Santa Monica, (213) 
394-5198. Style: Ethiopian nouvelle cuisine. Setting: Upper trendo with clay 
pots, burning frankincense and wise men. Recommended dishes: Assa wot (fish 
stew); yekik alitcha (puree of split peas); yemisir wot (thick lentil soup). 
Cost: $9-$20. 
</P>
<P>
India: Aashiana Cuisine of India, 11645 Wilshire Blvd., Los Angeles, 213) 
207-5522. Style: Familiar Indian menu plus a variety of fish dishes. Setting: 
Posh; view of Wilshire Boulevard. Recommended dishes: Fish Goa; calamari. Cost: 
$15-$35. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Drawing, TED ENGELBART 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
<TYPE>
<P>
Restaurant Review 
</P>
