<HEADLINE>
<P>
NONSMOKERS SPEAK OUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I was distressed and frustrated to read Dirlam's article. My husband and I are 
nonsmokers and travel a fair amount of miles. Due to my husband's illness (post 
open-heart surgery), we seek nonsmoking areas everywhere. It is not just a 
matter of preference, but of life and death! Why wasn't the airline named? Why 
should they be protected if the story was true? Please do not protect companies 
that have no regard for their customers. And do not publish such articles again 
unless companies are named. 
</P>
<P>
PAT SAX 
</P>
<P>
El Toro 
</P>
</TEXT>
