<HEADLINE>
<P>
NONSMOKERS SPEAK OUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Thank you for Sharon Dirlam's article, "A Nightmare Flight Leaves Nonsmokers 
Fuming" (Jan. 15). I could relate some other horror stories concerning groups. 
I have "no smoking" coaches on my tours, so I seldom have smokers on the trips. 
Also, I always book 28 no-smoking seats with the airlines when I plan the 
tours. 
</P>
<P>
However, on departure I have had many passengers placed in the smoking section. 
I no longer book the two air carriers that have let me down, and I let them 
know why. Airlines of other nations are the worst. I'll keep letting airlines 
know why I no longer book them for groups. Maybe we'll prevail. 
</P>
<P>
JANE E. HILLSEN 
</P>
<P>
Travel Today, 
</P>
<P>
Reminisce Tomorrow 
</P>
<P>
Redlands 
</P>
</TEXT>
