</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA020589-0125 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 14544 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
February 5, 1989, Sunday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Travel; Part 7; Page 20; Column 4; Travel Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
53 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
A SPECIAL KINDNESS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Anyone who could read "An Act of Kindness in 1933 Is Still Remembered" (Jan. 
22), by Bob O'Sullivan, and not be moved would be hard-hearted, indeed. That 
one act on the part of the manager of the Harvey House restaurant should have 
earned him a special visa through the pearly gates. 
</P>
<P>
HAROLD G. CONNOR 
</P>
<P>
La Habra 
</P>
</TEXT>
