<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEOPLE ON THE MOVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LINDA MARTINI-POSNER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
J. H. Snyder Co. of Los Angeles has a new partner, Ray Kaplan. He comes to the 
development company from the law firm of Rudin &amp; Appel. Kaplan's background 
includes 23 years of experience in business and real estate matters as a 
practicing attorney. 
</P>
<P>
David Meyers of Rancho Santa Fe has been named president of Watt Homes San 
Diego Inc., the newest home-building division of Watt Industries Inc. The focus 
of this division will be on affordable residential homes in San Diego and 
Riverside counties. Meyers' responsibilities will include acquisitions, 
development, sales and marketing. 
</P>
<P>
Jo Etta Bandy has become the Fullerton-based Covington Development Group's vice 
president of corporate communications. She will continue to oversee the 
company's investor relations programs, which she previously handled as 
director, and in her new capacity, she will also handle all general public 
relations and communicaitons matters. 
</P>
<P>
The Apartment Assn. of Greater Los Angeles has announced that Robert K. Green 
will serve as its seventh president. The association is the largest local 
apartment organization in the nation, with 25,000 members. Green was its first 
vice president in 1988 and secretary in 1986. 
</P>
<P>
Douglas Forker of Pasadena's Countrywide Funding Corp. will take on the 
responsibilities of production, underwriting and funding operations for the 
company's correspondent lending program in his newly appointed post as first 
vice president. 
</P>
<P>
The American Society of Real Estate Counselors has elected Ronald Buss to serve 
a three-year term on its board of governors. He is president of Buss-Shelger 
Associates, Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
Economics Research Associates' board of directors has a new president, Austin 
G. Anderson, and a new vice chairman, Wayne R. Wilson. Anderson will continue 
to be active in real estate economic planning and analysis while overseeing the 
firm's operations, and Wilson will be coordinating the development of new 
services in the recreation industry. 
</P>
<P>
Jimmie Nord has received appointment to the Code Review Subcommittee of the 
California Assn. of Hospitals and Health Systems. She is currently serving as 
professional education chairman of the National Assn. of Women in Construction. 
</P>
<P>
Sunland Consolidated Inc. of San Diego has created a new position of vice 
president and general counsel to be held by Scott Rollins. He will handle the 
company's legal and financing matters in land acquisitions, joint-venture 
formations and asset sales. 
</P>
<P>
The Sammis Co.'s Los Angeles/Ventura County office has a new senior vice 
president, William N. Eddy. Eddy will continue to oversee marketing programs 
for projects in the area. 
</P>
<P>
Donald J. Venitsky recently joined Cal-Pac Construction Inc. of Los Angeles as 
director of business development. He will manage the company's business in the 
commercial, medical, tenant improvement and renovation markets. LINDA 
MARTINI-POSNER 
</P>
</TEXT>
