<HEADLINE>
<P>
RAIN CAUSES DRAG RACES TO BE POSTPONED UNTIL NEXT WEEKEND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Heavy rains Saturday morning caused National Hot Rod Assn. officials to 
postpone qualifying and eliminations of the Chief Auto Parts Winternationals 
until next weekend on the Pomona Fairgrounds drag strip. 
</P>
<P>
Time trials will resume Friday with the second round of qualifying, followed by 
two more rounds Saturday. Speeds posted last Thursday in the first round will 
be carried over. The quickest 16 cars in top fuel, funny car and pro stock from 
the four rounds, as well as sportsman car qualifiers, will race next Sunday in 
side-by-side eliminations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
