<HEADLINE>
<P>
SDSU TOPS NORTHRIDGE IN MEN'S VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cal State Northridge, baffled by the serves of San Diego State, fell to the 
Aztecs, 15-11, 15-9, 9-15, 15-5, Saturday night in a Western Intercollegiate 
Volleyball Assn. match at SDSU. 
</P>
<P>
The Aztecs served 9 aces in the match and kept CSUN off balance with their 
change-of-speed serves. 
</P>
<P>
Cesar Mata had 4 aces and Sean Clark and Mike Mattarocci each had 2 for SDSU 
(2-1, 2-0 in conference play). 
</P>
<P>
Middle hitter Rafael Tulino had 16 kills in 19 attempts and outside hitter Bob 
Samuelson had a match-high 25 kills for CSUN (2-3, 0-3). 
</P>
