<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS' BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
DEFENSE KEYS OCEAN VIEW'S 52-38 VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ocean View High School forced Huntington Beach to try something new Saturday -- 
outside shooting. 
</P>
<P>
The Seahawks went to a 2-3 zone, halting the Oilers' inside game and limiting 
them to nine field goals in a 52-38 Sunset League victory before a capacity 
crowd at Ocean View. 
</P>
<P>
Huntington Beach (11-10, 7-2) made nine of 53 shots (17%) and didn't score from 
the field until almost two minutes into the second quarter. 
</P>
<P>
Ocean View (16-6, 6-2) kept the ball away from Jeff Long, who usually goes 
inside for easy layups. 
</P>
<P>
"Huntington Beach is excellent inside with their short baskets," Ocean View 
Coach Jim Harris said. "The idea was to not let that happen." 
</P>
<P>
Ocean View took a quick 12-3 lead in the first quarter, but at halftime, the 
Seahawks' lead was cut to two points, 23-21, thanks to the Oilers' 11 of 14 
free throw shooting. 
</P>
<P>
But Ocean View opened up a lead in the third quarter and coasted to the victory 
in the fourth. 
</P>
<P>
"We just didn't put the ball in the basket," Huntington Beach Coach Roy Miller 
said. "I've never had a team shoot that cold. 
</P>
<P>
"I don't know whether to attribute it to their defense or the fact that 
everyone decided to be cold. 
</P>
<P>
"I told the team that the pressure was on Ocean View. I told them to relax and 
have fun. But I was surprised at how tight we were." 
</P>
<P>
Ocean View didn't have a great shooting day either, connecting on 18 of 46 
attempts for 39%. 
</P>
<P>
But the Seahawks dominated the boards and got steady performances from Darren 
Ernst (11 points, 16 rebounds) and Greg Evans (game-high 15 points). 
</P>
<P>
Joey Kijewski led Huntington Beach with 11 points. 
</P>
<P>
LARRY NISTA 
</P>
<P>
Edison 48, Marina 46 -- Steve Thobe sank two free throws with 30 seconds left 
to put the Chargers up by six points as Edison (12-12, 5-3) withstood a late 
rally by Marina (2-6 in league play). Sean Hafelrig of Marina led all scorers 
with 13 points. 
</P>
<P>
Fountain Valley 66, Westminster 40 -- Mike Cook scored 15 points and pulled in 
10 rebounds to lead visiting Fountain Valley (17-5, 5-3). Don Shaw was 
Westminster's leading scorer with 14. 
</P>
<P>
In Olympic League boys' basketball: 
</P>
<P>
Orange Lutheran 83, Valley Christian 78 -- Pat Bagatourian led host Orange 
Lutheran (19-3, 12-0) with 30 points and teammate Daryl Cole added 24. Mike 
Blackstead was the leading scorer for Valley Christian (7-5, 16-6). 
</P>
<P>
Whittier Christian 99, Whitney 70 -- Whittier Christian had everybody score in 
a romp over Whitney at Sonora High School. Matt Riehm led the way with 27 
points and Paul McKinley added 21. Whittier Christian is 16-6, 9-3. Whitney 
(1-10 in league play) was led by Adrian Keller with 17 points. 
</P>
<P>
Ontario Christian 76, Capistrano Valley Christian 60 -- Jason Rodarmel led 
Capistrano Valley Christian (5-16, 2-10) with 15 points but it was not enough 
as the Eagles lost at home. 
</P>
<P>
Brethren 55, Santa Margarita 50 -- Dan Bathey led Santa Margarita (7-14, 2-10) 
with 18 points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
